<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900405-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>900405-0060.</DOCID><HL>   Bank of America Contract</HL><DATE>04/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BAC U.LLO F.CNC EUROP</CO><IN>BANKS (BNK)</IN><LP>   SAN FRANCISCO -- BankAmerica Corp.'s Bank of Americasubsidiary said it was awarded a contract from Severn RiverCrossing Ltd. to arrange $865 million for a bridge project inthe U.K.   Bank of America said it is lead underwriter for thefinancing, which involves bank debt jointly underwritten byLloyds Bank PLC of Britain and Caisse Nationale de CreditAgricole of France. Proceeds will be used to construct asecond bridge across the Severn river, and to refinancecurrent debt on the existing bridge. The new bridge will linkAvon in the west of England to Gwent in Wales, and willbecome part of Britain's M4 motorway.</LP><TEXT>   Severn River Crossing was established to hold a 30-yearconcession to design and build the new bridge, and operate italong with the new bridge.</TEXT></DOC>